flowRoot.flowPara: Self-organization is mediated by Hebbian learning, which adjusts connection weights after every saccade. The weights are constrained with divisive post-synaptic weight normalization per projection with learning rate .
Large spatial profile of divisive Pv-ir neurons causes weakly tuned response profiles, while subtractive Som-ir neurons develop strong orientation tuning due to their smaller integration area.
Relating the diversity of interneuronal subtypes to their functional roles in development, homeostasis and sensory processing
